Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, which focuses on information retrieval and search engines. The second most likely sub-category is cs.CL, which deals with computational linguistics and text analysis. The third most likely sub-category is cs.LG, which covers machine learning and data mining. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.HC, which studies human-computer interaction and user interfaces. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.DB, which addresses database systems and data management.
